ol.li: Block Alignment: Even with 0-byte input, the algorithm MUST produce exactly one 512-bit (64-byte) block.
Separator Necessity: The 0x80 byte ensures that an empty message "" results in a different padding pattern than a message containing a null byte "\0".
Endianness: The 64-bit length field at the end is stored in Big-Endian format per FIPS 180-4.
